COMMENT: The proton energy is known to better than 0.1%.
The listed uncertainties in the cross-section values are statistical only; 
the normalization uncertainty is ?5.0% (see "Sigma scale factor" fields). 
Note that the latter is a conservative estimate for the whole data set since 
the differential cross-section has been measured using a "relative" 
normalization procedure for the data up to 2.97 MeV (giving a normalization 
uncertainty of 2.0%) and an "absolute" normalization procedure for the data 
from 2.98 to 5.20 MeV (giving the quoted normalization uncertainty of 5.0%).  

